<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="927" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d927">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/94: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-31T08:00:00+03:00">October 31,
                                1943—8 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received 1:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1794. Personal for Secretary Morgenthau from the Secretary of State.</p>
                    <p>Delam 45. In reply to my oral and written representations on the subject, I
                        have received a letter from Molotov<note n="72" xml:id="d927fn72">Letter
                            dated October 30, 1943, not printed.</note> stating that the People’s
                        Commissariat of Finance will in the very near future send experts to
                        Washington to take part in the discussions concerning the International
                        Stabilization Fund.</p>
                    <p>Please repeat to Secretary Morgenthau in the event that he is not in
                        Washington. [Hull.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
            </body></text></TEI>